{"type":"message","id":"929f9d83","parentId":"53918c84","timestamp":"2026-02-01T02:10:47.186Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_0133KhKXf96zWNuMfj58JAjo","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Japan at night/Japan at Night 1.0.md:22:\t\t- Cash/Card issues in the yokochos\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Japanese Conversation Article.md:17:I've lived in the iroha-yokocho area of Sendai, an area packed with small 7-seater bars and restaurants, for about five years. I explore the side streets, have dinner and drinks, and hang around there at least three or four nights a week. If I plug in some conservative numbers (let's say three nights per week, three hours per excursion) that comes to nine hours per week, for fifty-two weeks, for five years. That comes to 2340 hours, most of which will be involved with some sort of social interaction with Japanese people. I would argue that the number is more like double that, but the order of magnitude sounds right.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//2024-04-15.md:32:In the evening I felt intense anxiety and tried to deal with it, but ended up going out anyway. I did a walk through [[„ÅÑ„Çç„ÅØÊ®™‰∏Å]] and so \n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Something Else.md:7:  Bunka_Yokocho(\"Bunka Yokocho\")\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Something Else.md:18:  Ali -->|Drinks and meets people| Bunka_Yokocho\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//2025-10-03.md:12:- The tale of Iroha Yokocho\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//The Doppleganger.md:25:Ikemoto-san got Airi up to pour a bottle onto the champagne tower, things were getting underway. We were surrounded by twenty-year-old girls in oiran (courtesan) style kimono, it was cheap and cheerful. We were in bunka yokocho, one of the oldest drinking alleys in Sendai. He ordered very expensive sushi for everyone from a traditional little place across the street.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//ia-writer-import/Question- Should I make three videos about debugging or just 1.md:20:\t* Daruma - In Bunka Yokocho, this is a charcoal yakiniku place that has been in Sendai since the 70s.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//ia-writer-import/I want to write more things.md:13:* Iroha yokocho\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//2024-03-30.md:13:After that I went to see [[Ê∏°ÈÇâÈ∫ªÈáåÂ≠ê|Mariko]] at the station and we talked about work and various things while checking out things around the new area in [[tekute]], near [[Sendai Station|the station]]. After that I met [[Jonathan Heap|Jon]] at [[the well]] in [[„ÅÑ„Çç„ÅØÊ®™‰∏Å]]. He bought me a couple of cans of Punk IPA and then we went to [[‰∏≠Âêâ]] where three people, [[Phil]], [[Johnny]], and [[Ryan]] also joined us. I got to know the owner of [[‰∏≠Âêâ]] and some random older lady, which is always a bad sign, but there were no problems this night.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Memoir/Chapter Listing.md:4:[[Memoir/Chapters/The Sharehouse|The Sharehouse]] - Moving into the sharehouse ‚Ä¢ Terashi ‚Ä¢ Ayumi Kimura ‚Ä¢ Covid repurcussions ‚Ä¢ Fuko Tsuchiya ‚Ä¢ Hostel Kiko ‚Ä¢ Osaka Boys ‚Ä¢ FITR 1113 and first steps to Iroha Yokocho.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Memoir/Chapter Listing.md:30:- Iroha Yokocho\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Memoir/Synopsis.md:13:This first act also where I'd end up in Iroha-yokocho, learning about the social culture of the side streets, starting at Jodan-sakaba. This would end in an incredible night with Arai Kyoko.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//2025-10-15.md:9:If I opened a small yokocho drinkery/eatery, what would be on the menu?\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Iroha Yokocho-8cc629f377f4413b9daefe3dbc84e5cd.md:1:# Iroha Yokocho\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Iroha Yokocho-8cc629f377f4413b9daefe3dbc84e5cd.md:3:Iroha Yokocho refers to a couple of \"yokocho\" or \"side alleys\" in Sendai in Ichibancho 2-chome. There are many small bars and restaurants there.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Iroha Yokocho-8cc629f377f4413b9daefe3dbc84e5cd.md:5:It is near to [[Bunka Yokocho]] and [[City House 506]]\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/daily-notes/2023-03-21.md:6:- I went to [[Lapis and Delica]], a new onigiri cafe in the yokochos, near [[Pizzeria Rocco]]\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/daily-notes/2023-11-19.md:13:  - I started the night out in [[Iroha Yokocho]] where I met [[Yamanami Airi]] and bought her dinner at [[Ittaku]]. I then met [[Konishi Shunji]] at [[Neiro]] where we had a complaining session about [[Wil Andrade]]. I should probably type more about [[Wil Andrade]] soon. I also discussed the situation around performance improvements with [[Konishi Shunji]] and he had a few suggestions:\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/daily-notes/2023-11-19.md:17:  - After that [[Konishi Shunji]] and I moved to [[Teeny]] where [[Yamanami Airi]] was working. [[Paul Amadio]] joined us later and it was difficult to get [[Konishi Shunji]] enjoying the conversation. We tried talking to [[Yamanami Airi]] and after one drink decided to attempt Garden in [[Bunka Yokocho]]. On the way there we went to [[Rock and Roll Bar]] and the owner, [[Shamoto Haru]] turned out to be good friends with [[Rumir]] which was upsetting for me. I will explain the whole Rumir saga at some point, but for more information, please see [[‚úåüèºSendai International Meetups: Origin Story]].\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Ittaku-c4d07b3fdbf040db9300c8eb9a67cec9.md:3:An italian restaurant in [[Iroha Yokocho]]\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Speed-running Sendai.md:7:Out of my mansion, if instead of turning left I go straight across the arcade, I have bunka yokocho and iroho yokocho in front of me (yokocho just means \"side street\"). These are picturesque Japanese side-streets packed with tiny little bars and restaurants that can only fit seven or eight people. There around 370 establishments like this in the yokochos. As I write this, if I look left from my screen and out of the window, I can see the glass canopy of the arcade a few meters in front of me and the tin roofs over the yokochos beyond it.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Speed-running Sendai.md:63:This night starts the same way as most nights start in [[Sendai]] for me: it's the evening, I'm not with my boys, and I'm both hungry and a bit lonely, so I'll go out to one of the yokochos for a bite to eat and maybe a drink or two. The first place I try is a shochu place with a wiry master is his late fifties, it's cheap, the food is amazing and the regular customers are all friends.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Speed-running Sendai.md:79:Satoru decides he doesn't have the appetite for a night out with me, but the salarymen are down. Once we settle the bill at venue 1 we leave the yokochos and head up to Toichi ichiba. I start getting to know them. One of them is a sales director and is worried about an overall economic downturn. This one strikes me as a particularly bad drunk. The other one is here on tanshin funin and misses his family back in Chiba prefecture.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Bunka Yokocho-278adea573824bda86e44a0d37f46f9e.md:1:# Bunka Yokocho\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Teeny-9daac37a10ff4e5faca0a212703f516d.md:5:- Location: [[Iroha Yokocho]], [[Sendai]]\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Yamanami Airi.md:5:Airi is the proprietor and operator of [[teeny...i]], a whisky bar in [[„ÅÑ„Çç„ÅØÊ®™‰∏Å|Iroha Yokocho]].\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//2025-11-01.md:20:- Cash situation for the yokochos\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Lecture at Rinri Houjinkai.md:43:- Going out to meet people, yokochos, etc - bunka\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//„ÅÑ„Çç„ÅØÊ®™‰∏Å.md:7:  - Iroha Yokocho\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Another day in my strange life in Japan.md:79:Back in Iroha Yokocho I walked around trying to figure out what I wanted to do. I was a bit restless and hungry. The yokochos were quiet, and Tori Yoshi was quiet, with a group of three salaryman at the end of the counter and no one else in the shop, so I thought it might be a good chance to show face have a relaxed meal, encompassing the jagamaru.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Another day in my strange life in Japan.md:83:After the second world war, Iroha-yokocho emerged as two streets, one a market with some goods prohibited by the occupation, the other with a row of restaurants and drinky bars. The area was administered and supported by the Matsuo-gumi Yakuza group, by their oyabun and a young captain that had made a name for himself by establishing the market. 35 years ago that captain or _wakagashira_ started a yakitori restaurant on the northern Aoba-dori side alley, the place was called Tori Yoshi. Tori Yoshi is now an _institution_ in Sendai, one of the most storied yakitori restaurants we have.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Another day in my strange life in Japan.md:133:Three or four years ago I was in Jaco, a shochu bar in the Yokochos. The master was playing _Once Upon a Time in Hollywood_ muted on a small TV at the end of the bar, The Beatles *Norweigan Wood* on the sound system, and I was drinking a fruity wheat shochu while enjoying some goya champuru. Whisps of eggy egg with bitter strands of goya and a magical chilli oil that tasted alcoholic."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9