{"type":"message","id":"d5aa0db1","parentId":"ccf7c3b8","timestamp":"2026-02-01T02:10:51.388Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_018hkZJQJXv64EZ9vkRo6cPN","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//FR from Landrue Nov 2024.md:5:There was still a lot of good stuff out considering the comparatively low population of Sendai. It was the old Sendai I remember in reality. Over the course of three days I got around 60 approaches in. My wings did a few but are a bit more picky than I am. I spent a majority of Thursday and Friday sleeping. Saturday I got up early after a solid 12 hours of sleep and changed hotels to one super close to Kokubuncho. My hotel before this was about the same distance but it sucked ass and the room was set to boiling temperature with no way to control the thermostat.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//FR from Landrue Nov 2024.md:9:We approach around Sendai but not much is biting. I would probably do double the amount of approaches when free like I was while traveling with prime logistics...but we take a break and go back to our hotels. We set a meet time for 18:30 bwfore kayaba rush at 19:00 but both of us are too horny to stay indoors for long. I used my break time to empty my lungs as best I can, chug some meds, and text the few Lines I got over the day. „Åæ„ÅÑ the snl girl (also my regs name) gets back to me she is done shopping and free. I invite her to Kokubuncho which in our short convo I had said we were heading there to drink and ÈÅä„Å∂. She thinks it's scary etc. She almost canceles right there but somehow I breath some life back into it (will post chat log later). I invite her to this „Ç∑„Éº„Ç∑„É£ place in Sendai that is a dope spot and I wanted to go to anyways. If she noped out I was still going so no harm done. \n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//FR from Landrue Nov 2024.md:13:My plan here was to walk right to the lovehotel to prompt the genkan freeze I felt was coming so I could go party with my boys. But a few seconds after leaving she asks where my hotel is. So I walk right past the main Kokubuncho LH and walk the five blocks over to my hotel. \n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Velours Sendai.md:8:area: ÂõΩÂàÜÁî∫\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Experiments in mindfulness.md:1:I sat in the dim red light of the shisha bar in the Kokubuncho district of Sendai, Japan with my good friend James. He was upset. I'd said a bit too much, pried a bit too deeply, and now he was visibly agitated. He wasn't ready.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Something Else.md:8:  Kokubuncho(\"Kokubuncho\")\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Something Else.md:19:  Ali -->|Explores night life| Kokubuncho\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Middle Mix.md:2:area: ÂõΩÂàÜÁî∫\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//ia-writer-import/Drunk with Vishal.md:56:But, I'm not so inclined, and wasn't inclined either on that cold spring night walking Victor safely in the direction of his mansion on the way home from Kokubuncho. He had been stumbling in the wrong direction when I found him, and I offered to walk him back towards his place. It was an offer I ended up regretting.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//ia-writer-import/Drunk with Vishal.md:88:From where I picked him up in Kokubuncho I got him safely to Sendai station. If it had been raining I would have offered to take him all the way back to his place, but the chat appeared to have sobered him up.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//ia-writer-import/Hi all, this is a quick write-up of our meet on 14th June 2022.md:7:* üç∏ After the meetup finished, a small group of us ventured to Kokubuncho to sample the Sendai night scene.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//ia-writer-import/Moeka, Marina, Kana, at Choutsugahi.md:89:She asked if I was in Sendai and I said yes, surprised to hear from her. She said she was in Kokubuncho right now and was wondering if I was out. I said yes and met her at a Daikoku, and we got caught up.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//ia-writer-import/OK so let‚Äôs do a bit of reflection and planning.md:21:If I think about it there‚Äôs actually no reason for me to ever go to Kokubuncho. Literally none. All my drinking could be done outside of Bee. It‚Äôs just so fucking stupid. So much money. I need to be serious about my money, maybe that‚Äôs what I need to focus on.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//ia-writer-import/How to speak Japanese the hard way.md:24:* Kokubuncho 2-chome (buncho)\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//ia-writer-import/Work Ramp Up May 27th 20202.md:7:* üçπ After the event wrapped up, a phew of us decamped to La Rose, a standing bar in Kokubuncho.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Sendai International Meetups - Origin Story.md:59:But, I'm not so inclined, and wasn't inclined either on that cold spring night walking [[Vishal]] safely in the direction of his mansion on the way home from Kokubuncho. He had been stumbling in the wrong direction when I found him, and I offered to walk him back towards his place. It was an offer I ended up regretting.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Sendai International Meetups - Origin Story.md:91:From where I picked him up in Kokubuncho I got him safely to [[Sendai]] station. If it had been raining I would have offered to take him all the way back to his place, but the chat appeared to have sobered him up.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/daily-notes/2023-11-19.md:23:  - After that I gave her some taxi money and saw her off at [[Sendai Station]]. In the same taxi I alone went back to Kokubuncho to meet up with everyone. It turned out that [[Mandory]] had had sex with [[Hosoi Tomoho]] and [[Paul Amadio]] had had sex with [[Mito Yuriko]], which means that my friends had sex with girls that I approach almost simultaneously with me. Concurrent nampa. Monstrous savagery. To the victor the spoils. This feels like the beginning of a new era.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/‚úåüèºSendai International Meetups: Origin Story-0e401747279c4b209b23e3e3982e1c2f.md:59:But, I'm not so inclined, and wasn't inclined either on that cold spring night walking [[Vishal]] safely in the direction of his mansion on the way home from Kokubuncho. He had been stumbling in the wrong direction when I found him, and I offered to walk him back towards his place. It was an offer I ended up regretting.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/‚úåüèºSendai International Meetups: Origin Story-0e401747279c4b209b23e3e3982e1c2f.md:91:From where I picked him up in Kokubuncho I got him safely to [[Sendai]] station. If it had been raining I would have offered to take him all the way back to his place, but the chat appeared to have sobered him up.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Speed-running Sendai.md:9:If we go back to the original left past the designer stores, walk straight through the arcade for about seven minutes, we end up in Kokubuncho, the central entertainment area in Sendai. Kokubuncho is a relatively safe area¬π to walk around in. As a foreigner the kyacchi won't bother you much, and getting drugged and tricked out of huge sums of money is practically unheard of. The area is filled with hostess clubs, girls bars, snack bars and regular drinking establishments. More than you could visit if you went out every night for an year, but not enough to keep you busy for three.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Speed-running Sendai.md:111:There's a very high-end snack bar in kokubuncho, it doesn't show up on maps. It's run by a 42-year old mama who wears a kimono, sings old songs on the karaoke machine and occasionally plays the shamisen. She's known for her beauty and hospitality. However her husband died a few years ago, and her boyfriend (who she didn't actually stop seeing while married) passed away a few months after that. A third man in her life passed away within the same year. Her snack is bar is dark, with expensive whiskeys, rare blended shochus and kokubuncho yakuza and company directors (line is blurry there) as her customers.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Speed-running Sendai.md:117:We walk over to her bar in kokubuncho and she greets me at the door. She's not in a kimono, but I remember she told me it's because her excema was playing up. I ask about that and after her six-year old daughter, who she keeps in a night nursery while she works (very common set up for night workers who are also mothers).\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Speed-running Sendai.md:127:We leave the den of evil and head a bit further down Kokubuncho-dori. Some of the experienced kyacchi greet me and ask me what I'm up to tonight. We know each other by name at this point. I've drunk with a handful of them at very sketchy places over the years.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Speed-running Sendai.md:141:The DJ is great. 90s hip-hop, lots of 2Pac and Biggie, modern pop too, it's like he is in my on repeat playlist. After an hour I decide I'm tired and I'm ready to go home. We settle up and the girls see us off at the elevator. Sasaki-san decides to go home so I wave goodbye to him. I walk back down Kokubuncho street on the way back to my place.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Speed-running Sendai.md:179:Retsuko-mama is the aforementioned \"last boss\" of Kokubuncho. Politicians curry favour with her, she is the \"fixer\" behind the scenes and no big deals get done in [[Sendai]] without her knowing about them. Her exploits and wealth are of legend. Godmother, don, powerbroker, call her what you will, but a good business card to have in your wallet, let's put it that way.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Speed-running Sendai.md:189:I say OK, but decide I'll head back to mine first and maybe fall asleep. About 90m later she calls me, she's very drunk and clearly not well. I come back to Kokubuncho street and meet her walking in the opposite direction. She has a miserable look on her face, her makeup is smeared as though she's been crying, and there's a red stain on her all-white top.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//reflect-import/reflect-alinajaf-20240430-2205-v1.0/Steal from my repertoire-4b0a67446f9c44f7ba78da5cd0f2d62a.md:35:    - Could be Ê≠åËàû‰ºéÁî∫, ‰∏≠Ê¥≤, ËñÑÈáé, ÂõΩÂàÜÁî∫, etc"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":232,"aggregated":"/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//FR from Landrue Nov 2024.md:5:There was still a lot of good stuff out considering the comparatively low population of Sendai. It was the old Sendai I remember in reality. Over the course of three days I got around 60 approaches in. My wings did a few but are a bit more picky than I am. I spent a majority of Thursday and Friday sleeping. Saturday I got up early after a solid 12 hours of sleep and changed hotels to one super close to Kokubuncho. My hotel before this was about the same distance but it sucked ass and the room was set to boiling temperature with no way to control the thermostat.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//FR from Landrue Nov 2024.md:9:We approach around Sendai but not much is biting. I would probably do double the amount of approaches when free like I was while traveling with prime logistics...but we take a break and go back to our hotels. We set a meet time for 18:30 bwfore kayaba rush at 19:00 but both of us are too horny to stay indoors for long. I used my break time to empty my lungs as best I can, chug some meds, and text the few Lines I got over the day. „Åæ„ÅÑ the snl girl (also my regs name) gets back to me she is done shopping and free. I invite her to Kokubuncho which in our short convo I had said we were heading there to drink and ÈÅä„Å∂. She thinks it's scary etc. She almost canceles right there but somehow I breath some life back into it (will post chat log later). I invite her to this „Ç∑„Éº„Ç∑„É£ place in Sendai that is a dope spot and I wanted to go to anyways. If she noped out I was still going so no harm done. \n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//FR from Landrue Nov 2024.md:13:My plan here was to walk right to the lovehotel to prompt the genkan freeze I felt was coming so I could go party with my boys. But a few seconds after leaving she asks where my hotel is. So I walk right past the main Kokubuncho LH and walk the five blocks over to my hotel. \n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Velours Sendai.md:8:area: ÂõΩÂàÜÁî∫\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Experiments in mindfulness.md:1:I sat in the dim red light of the shisha bar in the Kokubuncho district of Sendai, Japan with my good friend James. He was upset. I'd said a bit too much, pried a bit too deeply, and now he was visibly agitated. He wasn't ready.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Something Else.md:8:  Kokubuncho(\"Kokubuncho\")\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Something Else.md:19:  Ali -->|Explores night life| Kokubuncho\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//Middle Mix.md:2:area: ÂõΩÂàÜÁî∫\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//ia-writer-import/Drunk with Vishal.md:56:But, I'm not so inclined, and wasn't inclined either on that cold spring night walking Victor safely in the direction of his mansion on the way home from Kokubuncho. He had been stumbling in the wrong direction when I found him, and I offered to walk him back towards his place. It was an offer I ended up regretting.\n/Users/najafali/Desktop/ali-vault//ia-writer-import/Drunk with Vishal.md:88:From where I picked him up in Kokubuncho I got him safely to Sendai station. If it had been raining I would ha