{"type":"message","id":"81392b4b","parentId":"e8ee2ad8","timestamp":"2026-02-01T02:11:10.039Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01B6XFcWWstzZMgxQXTWa7Fo","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"_Japan at Night 1.0 is a project collecting work items that get the tour business to a systemised, professional, and ready for marketing outside of Viator_\n# Task List\n\nBelow is a general list of tasks for this iteration of the system. The emphasis is on building systems and slightly increasing the tour experience. The idea is to prepare us for the next sprint: the marketing push.\n\n## Lead Magnet and Marketing Funnel\n- Create an initial _lead magnet_: An extensive PDF guide to drinking and eating at night in Sendai for anyone that registers their email address.\n- Set up a 2-email basic funnel for anyone that wants to set up a tour. Also a contact form, inbound email address, or the ability to set up a call to discuss a tour booking if they want to, no-obligation, completely free.\n- Provide functionality for users to leave reviews of the tour, potentially using trustpilot or something like it.\n- Create a _landing page_ for the tour that persuades the reader to sign up for a tour with Japan at night. They should be able to book their tour directly from the landing page.\n- For marketing the tour, come up with a _logotype_ for use on the website, online marketing, and branded goods.\n- Think about the _brand_ Japan at Night, and come up with some _brand guidelines_ for online communication. Think Anthony Bourdain, Somebody Feed Phil, and my special mix of charisma, Japanese ability, and love for Japanese culture. This means figuring out a mission statement for the company, and clarity on values for our offering and operations.\n## Sales and bookings\n- Accept direct bookings and stripe payments on the `japanatnight.tours` platform.\n- Make sure the platform is fully multi-lingual, ready for all languages for all internal and external facing